# ammannweb

One-page marketing site for **Oliver Ammann**’s solo web-design side business (Vereine + small businesses), based in **Frauenfeld, Thurgau, Schweiz**. Language: **German (Swiss)** for all user-facing copy.

- **Repo:** https://github.com/oliver-ammann/ammannweb-homepage
- **Production URL:** https://ammannweb.ch
- **Contact email:** contact@ammannweb.ch

## Stack

React 18 · Vite 6 · TypeScript · Tailwind 4 · React Router 7 · static SPA on Vercel.

```bash
npm install && npm run dev    # http://localhost:5173
npm run build                 # tsc + vite build → dist/
```

Do not add backend, CMS runtime, or heavy dependencies unless explicitly requested.

## Layout & routing

Home sections (order matters): **Hero → Pricing → Process → Benefits → Services → Contact**.

| Route | File |
|-------|------|
| `/` | `src/app/pages/HomePage.tsx` |
| `/impressum` | `src/app/pages/ImpressumPage.tsx` |
| `/datenschutz` | `src/app/pages/DatenschutzPage.tsx` |
| `/agb` | `src/app/pages/AgbPage.tsx` |

Sections live in `src/app/components/sections/`. Layout: `Nav`, `Footer`, `LegalLayout`. SPA rewrites in `vercel.json`.

## Config — edit these, not hardcoded duplicates

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/app/constants.ts` | Brand color, CTA labels, `SITE` (email/url/location), nav links |
| `src/app/legal-config.ts` | Legal entity (Impressum, AGB, Datenschutz) |
| `src/app/profile-config.ts` | Bio, role, photo path |
| `.env.example` | `VITE_CONTACT_EMAIL`, `VITE_SITE_URL` |

Keep legal and pricing facts in sync across pages.

## Business & copy guardrails

**Positioning:** Vereine and small businesses. Solo operator — personal, direct, not agency-scale.

**Pricing (fixed, no hourly):**
- Website: **CHF 900** one-time
- Retainer: **CHF 79/month** — **technical only** (hosting, updates, CMS uptime). Client edits content in CMS themselves. Not content editing or handyman work.

**Do not reintroduce:**
- Portfolio / case-study section (no projects yet)
- Tech-stack showcase section
- Delivery time promises (“Prototyp in 24h”, stats)
- Hourly billing language
- Google Fonts CDN — fonts are **self-hosted** via `@fontsource/dm-sans` in `src/styles/fonts.css`

**Tone:** Light, trustworthy Swiss German. One intentional humor line lives in `profile-config.ts` bio (+ optional Berg reference in form thank-you). Do not scatter agency-bashing elsewhere.

**CTA labels:** Nav/buttons → `Anfrage senden` (`CTA_LABEL`). Form submit → `Nachricht senden` (`FORM_SUBMIT_LABEL`).

**AGB:** Retainer price references the **website-published price at contract time**, not a hardcoded CHF 79 in legal text.

## Contact

- Form: FormSubmit.co via `src/app/utils/contact.ts` — no API key; first live submit activates email.
- Contact: form + email via `ContactChannels.tsx`.

## Styling conventions

- Brand red: `#D4621A` (`BRAND_RED`)
- Font: DM Sans (`FONT_FAMILY`)
- Most components use **inline `style` props**, not Tailwind classes — match existing sections when editing UI
- Minimize diff scope; reuse `scrollToId`, existing layout patterns

## Legal / privacy

Datenschutz must disclose FormSubmit + Vercel hosting. Fonts are self-hosted (no Google Fonts section). Update `legal-config.ts` placeholders (street, UID, phone) before go-live.

## Pre-go-live checklist (user-owned)

- Fill `legal-config.ts` street address
- Add `public/profile.jpg`, set `photoSrc` in `profile-config.ts`
- Deploy on Vercel with env vars; confirm FormSubmit activation

## Git & deployment

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| **`develop`** | Day-to-day work — commit and push here |
| **`main`** | Production — **only** via PR from `develop` (no direct pushes) |

- Vercel: **`main`** → production (`ammannweb.ch` / production URL); **`develop`** → preview deployments.
- Ship to production: type **`/ship`** or **`ship`** in Cursor (see `.cursor/commands/ship.md`). Optional: `npm run ship -- --build "message"`.
- After merge to `main`, production redeploys from Git automatically.

## Linear (work tracking)

**Linear is the source of truth** for client work and operational tasks. Inbound client projects land in Linear (not ad-hoc in chat).

- **Marketing site (this repo):** issues in an internal / `ammannweb` Linear project → `ammannweb-homepage` on GitHub.
- **Each client website:** **new Linear project** + **new Git repo** from [`client-site-template`](https://github.com/oliver-ammann/client-site-template) (never client code in `ammannweb-homepage`).
- When the user references an issue (e.g. `AMM-12` or a client project issue), use Linear MCP to read status, description, and acceptance criteria before coding — and confirm **which repo** to use.
- PR titles/bodies may reference the Linear issue ID; prefer closing/moving the issue when work ships.
- Do not invent client scope — if unclear, ask or read the Linear issue.

## Agent defaults

- **Branch:** Check out `develop` for changes; never commit or push directly to `main` unless the user explicitly asks.
- **Linear:** Check issue context for client or tracked tasks; keep plugin enabled in Cursor.
- Prefer config files over scattering magic strings
- Keep README accurate when changing features or env vars
- Do not commit `.env`, secrets, or `dist/`, or `.cursor/`
- Only create git commits when the user asks
